data.name: Grilled Fish Burrito

ingredients.name: white fish fillets (like tilapia or cod)

data.quickTastyDescription: A deliciously fresh grilled fish wrapped in a warm tortilla with zesty toppings.
detailedCookingInstructions: Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.
Brush the fish fillets with olive oil and season with salt, pepper, and juice from half the lime.
Grill the fish for about 5-7 minutes on each side until cooked through and flaky.
While the fish is grilling, prepare the tortillas by warming them on the grill or in a pan for a minute on each side.
Once the fish is done, remove it from the grill and chop into bite-sized pieces.
To assemble the burritos, place grilled fish in the center of a tortilla, add shredded cabbage, salsa, diced avocado, chopped cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice.
Fold the sides of the tortilla over the filling and roll it tightly to form the burrito.
Serve immediately, with extra salsa on the side if desired.
data.detailedName: Grilled Fish Burrito with Avocado and Cilantro
